taxicabs with the words “White Only” in August 1962</span> <span class="attribution__credit">Warren K Leffler/PhotoQuest/Getty Images</span></figcaption></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" height="710" width="1024" data-id="56531" src="https://www.propublica.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Albany-Day-2-Chapter-3-005.jpg?w=1024" alt="A group of men huddle around a pool table looking toward the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. and the Rev. Ralph Abernathy.
